This paper deals with the problem of training machine learning models incrementally using active learning with access to imperfect or noisy oracles. The paper specifically considers the setting of batch active learning, which is related to machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The experiments are conducted on benchmark image classification datasets (MNIST, SVHN, and CIFAR10), which are related to computer vision (cs.CV) and natural language processing (cs.CL). The paper also introduces an extra denoising layer to deep networks, which is related to data structures (cs.DS). Therefore, the most likely arXiv CS sub-categories for this paper are cs.LG and cs.AI, followed by cs.CV, cs.CL, and cs.DS.
